nt(f\"💬 A: {entry['answer']}\")\n\nprint(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 70)\nprint(\"Review complete. Proceed to Cell 14 if answers look good.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-24T13:03:33.339427Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-24T13:03:33.339809Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-24T13:03:33.346861Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-24T13:03:33.339787Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-24T13:03:33.345921Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"\n======================================================================\n         COMPLETE ANSWER REVIEW (Q01 – Q15)\n======================================================================\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n🔹 Q01 [IN SCOPE ✅]\n❓ Q: What is the probation period for new employees at Zyro Dynamics?\n💬 A: The probation period for new employees at Zyro Dynamics is 6 months, starting from their date of joining, as stated in the 09_Onboarding_and_Separation_Policy document. However, it may be extended by up to 3 months if performance has not met the expected standard during the initial period.\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n🔹 Q02 [IN SCOPE ✅]\n❓ Q: How many earned leaves are employees entitled to per year?\n💬 A: According to the 02_Leave_Policy document (Page 1), employees are entitled to 15 days of Earned Leave upon completion of one year of continuous service. Thereafter, Earned Leave accrues at the rate of 1.25 days per month.\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n🔹 Q03 [IN SCOPE ✅]\n❓ Q: What is the work-from-home policy for Zyro Dynamics employees?\n💬 A: According to the Work From Home Policy (Doc Code: ZDL-HR-003, Version: V.02, Effective Date: 01 March 2025), Zyro Dynamics recognizes the importance of flexible work arrangements for employee wellbeing, productivity, and retention. The policy establishes a structured framework for employees to work from a location other than their designated Zyro Dynamics office, with the expectation that all WFH arrangements will be exercised responsibly and that the quality and timeliness of work will not be compromised. (Source: 03_Work_From_Home_Policy)\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n🔹 Q04 [IN SCOPE ✅]\n❓ Q: What are the performance rating categories used in the annual performance review?\n💬 A: I'm sorry, I couldn't find this information in Zyro Dynamics' HR policy documents. The provided context mentions a rating scale with ratings of 1, 2, 4, and 5, but it does not provide a comprehensive list of performance rating categories.\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n🔹 Q05 [IN SCOPE ✅]\n❓ Q: What is the reimbursement limit for domestic travel at Zyro Dynamics?\n💬 A: The reimbursement limits for domestic travel at Zyro Dynamics vary by grade level. According to the Travel and Expense Policy (Doc Code: ZDL-FIN-001), the domestic travel entitlements are as follows:\n\n- For L1 to L2: Hotel per night - Rs. 2,000, Daily Allowance - Rs. 500\n- For L3 to L4: Hotel per night - Rs. 3,500, Daily Allowance - Rs. 700\n- For L5 to L6: Hotel per night - Rs. 5,000, Daily Allowance - Rs. 1,000\n- For L7 to L8: Hotel per night - Rs. 7,500, Daily Allowance - Rs. 1,500\n- For L9 to L10: Hotel per night - Rs. 12,000, Daily Allowance - Rs. 2,500\n\nPlease refer to the Travel and Expense Policy document for more details.\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n🔹 Q06 [IN SCOPE ✅]\n❓ Q: What action can be taken against an employee who violates the code of conduct?\n💬 A: I'm sorry, I couldn't find this information in Zyro Dynamics' HR policy documents. However, I can provide information on the consequences of proven misconduct under the Prevention of Sexual Harassment Policy, as stated in Source 1: 08_Prevention_of_Sexual_Harassment_Policy. According to this policy, the Company may impose actions such as a written warning with mandatory completion of a sensitisation and inclusion training programme, depending on the gravity of the proven misconduct.\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n🔹 Q07 [IN SCOPE ✅]\n❓ Q: What is the maternity leave entitlement at Zyro Dynamics?\n💬 A: According to the Leave Policy document (Source 2: 02_Leave_Policy | Page 2), female employees who have completed a minimum of 80 days of service in the 12 months preceding the expected date of delivery are entitled to 26 weeks of paid Maternity Leave, in accordance with the Maternity Benefit (Amendment) Act, 2017. This entitlement applies to the first two live births. For a third child, the entitlement is 12 weeks.\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n🔹 Q08 [IN SCOPE ✅]\n❓ Q: How should an employee report a sexual harassment complaint?\n💬 A: To report a sexual harassment complaint, an employee can contact the Internal Complaints Committee (ICC) at icc@zyrodynamics.com or submit a complaint in a sealed envelope addressed to the Presiding Officer at the HR office at Zyro Dynamics HQ, as stated in the Prevention of Sexual Harassment Policy (Source 5: 08_Prevention_of_Sexual_Harassment_Policy | Page 1). Additionally, employees can also reach out to hr.grievance@acruxdynamics.com for grievances and complaints, including ICC/POSH related matters, as mentioned in the Employee Handbook (Source 2: 01_Employee_Handbook | Page 3).\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n🔹 Q09 [IN SCOPE ✅]\n❓ Q: What are the IT security responsibilities of Zyro Dynamics employees?\n💬 A: According to the \"IT and Data Security Policy\" (Source 1: 07_IT_and_Data_Security_Policy | Page 0), the purpose of this policy is to protect the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of all information assets owned, managed, or processed by Zyro Dynamics Pvt. Ltd. Although the document does not explicitly outline the specific IT security responsibilities of employees, it does establish the standards for acceptable use of company IT systems, data, and network infrastructure, and defines the responsibilities of all users in protecting these assets. \n\nFor detailed responsibilities, I would recommend referring to the full \"IT and Data Security Policy\" document (ZDL-IT-001).\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n🔹 Q10 [IN SCOPE ✅]\n❓ Q: What is the full and final settlement process when an employee resigns?\n💬 A: According to the 09_Onboarding_and_Separation_Policy (Page 2), the full and final settlement process involves the following steps:\n\n1. Obtain financial clearance (advances, loans, expenses) from Finance, which should be done 3 days before the last working day.\n2. Revoke all system access and credentials by IT on the last working day.\n3. Attend an exit interview with HR during the final week of employment.\n4. Receive a relieving letter from HR after the full and final settlement is processed.\n\nNote that the exact timeline for the full and final settlement process is not specified, but it is mentioned that the relieving letter will be issued by HR after the settlement is processed.\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n🔹 Q11 [OUT OF SCOPE 🚫]\n❓ Q: What is the current stock price of Infosys?\n💬 A: I'm sorry, but I can only answer HR-related questions based on Zyro Dynamics' official policy documents. Your question appears to be outside the scope of HR policies. Please reach out to the HR team directly for other queries, or ask me about topics like leave policy, compensation, work-from-home rules, performance reviews, or employee conduct.\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n🔹 Q12 [IN SCOPE ✅]\n❓ Q: Can you recommend a good Python course for data science?\n💬 A: I'm sorry, I couldn't find this information in Zyro Dynamics' HR policy documents.\n\n───────────────